{
  "_comment": "Registry of every locale the landing page is built for. `code` is the URL path segment (/xx/) and the hreflang value; the English `en` locale is served from the site root (/). `name` is the endonym shown in the language switcher and the cross-language banner; `flag` is the emoji shown beside it. `og_locale` feeds <meta property=og:locale>. `script` picks which webfont subsets to preload (latin1 | latinext | cyrillic | greek); every page can still render any glyph via the unicode-range @font-face rules, this just preloads the common case. Order here drives the switcher + sitemap order. To add a language: append an entry and drop a matching strings/<code>.json next to en.json — nothing else to wire up.",
